## 2. UI/UX Design Patterns

### 2.1 Layout System

**Master Layout** ([app.blade.php](file:///d:/xampp/htdocs/gocsach-laravel/resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php)):
- **Font Stack:** Merriweather (serif for headings) + Nunito Sans (sans for body)
- **Color Palette:**
  - `brand-green: #2A483A` — Primary (deep forest green)
  - `brand-cream: #FDFBF7` — Background
  - `brand-beige: #F2E8DC` — Accent background
  - `brand-accent: #D4A373` — CTA / highlight (warm gold)
- **Framework:** Tailwind CSS via CDN with custom config
- **Structure:** `@include('partials.header')` → `@yield('content')` → `@include('partials.footer')` → `@include('partials.chatbox')`
- **Global includes:** Report modal on every page, seasonal decorations, AI chatbot

> **Movie Port Color Adaptation:**
> - Replace green palette with a dark cinema palette: `#1a1a2e` (dark navy), `#16213e` (midnight blue), `#e94560` (accent red)
> - Keep the warm accent approach but shift to a cinematic feel
> - Fonts: Inter or Outfit (modern) + Playfair Display (serif for titles)

### 2.2 Homepage Sections (1,767 lines of UI)

The homepage is a **content-rich magazine layout** with a 12-column grid (8+4 split):

| Section | Description | Movie Adaptation |
|---------|------------|-----------------|
| **Hero Carousel** | Full-width banner slider with book covers, ratings, 3D hover effect, navigation dots | →  Trending movies with backdrop images, trailers |
| **Featured Articles** | 3+2 grid (featured + sidebar articles) | → Film news & editorials |
| **Book Review Slider** | Horizontal scroll cards with tabs (Latest / Hot), badges (NEW/HOT) | → Review slider with movie posters |
| **New Books Slider** | Horizontal scroll of book covers with hover overlays | → "Now Playing" / "Coming Soon" carousels |
| **Community Reviews** | AJAX-loaded comment feed with sort (Latest/Popular), pagination | → Community discussion feed |
| **Challenge Banner** | Gamification event CTA with trophy icon, gradient background | → "Watch Challenge" events |
| **Daily Quote** (sidebar) | Rotating daily literary quote | → Movie quote of the day |
| **"What to Read Today?"** (sidebar) | Random book recommendation | → "Random Movie Pick" |
| **Daily Author** (sidebar) | Featured author profile | → Featured Director / Actor |
| **Community Stats** (sidebar) | Real-time counts (books, members, reviews, online users) | → Movie stats dashboard |
| **Category Explorer** (sidebar) | Genre/category listing with book counts | → Genre explorer |

### 2.3 Component Patterns

#### Card Components
- **Book Card:** Aspect ratio 2:3, rounded corners, rating badge (top-right), "NEW" badge (top-left), gradient overlay on hover, quick-action button on hover
- **Review Card:** 16:10 aspect ratio, backdrop gradient, user avatar, star rating, view count
- **Article Card:** Full-bleed image with text overlay, tag badge, author + date metadata

#### Interaction Patterns
- **Star Rating Display:** Full/half/empty star rendering using Font Awesome (`fa-star`, `fa-star-half-alt`, `far fa-star`)
- **Like Toggle:** AJAX POST with optimistic UI update, heart icon animation
- **Bookmark/Save:** Toggle with toast notification
- **Horizontal Sliders:** Scroll-based with prev/next buttons (visible on hover), no-scrollbar CSS
- **AJAX Pagination:** Comment feed loads via AJAX, partial view returned
- **Report Modal:** Global modal on every page for reporting content
- **Tab Switching:** CSS-based active state with smooth transitions

#### Decorative Elements
- Blurred gradient circles (`.blur-2xl`, `.blur-3xl`) as background decorations
- Subtle pattern overlays on hero sections
- `animate-pulse` on NEW/HOT badges
- `transition-all duration-500` with `hover:scale-105` on cards
- Seasonal decorations (Christmas snow, Tet fireworks, Valentine hearts)

### 2.4 Responsive Design

- **Breakpoints:** xs:400px, sm:640px, md:768px, lg:1024px, xl:1280px
- **Mobile menu:** Slide-in panel from right with backdrop overlay, ESC to close
- **Grid adapts:** 1 column mobile → 12-column desktop (8+4 sidebar)
- **Cards:** Adjust width (w-32 → w-44) and visibility of elements across breakpoints
- **Safe area padding** for iOS notch

